@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### User Sign Up (Owner - default role)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "owner1@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "name": "Owner One"
}

###
### User Login (Owner) - returns access_token and refresh_token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "owner1@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

###
### Refresh access token (use refresh_token from login/register; optional ?rotate=false to reuse same refresh token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###
### Host Sign Up (register, then promote to HOST via admin)
### Step 1: Register as normal user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "host1@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "name": "Host One"
}

###
### Host Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "host1@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

###
### Admin Sign Up (initial admin via register, then role updated with admin.http)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin1@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "name": "Admin One"
}

###
### Admin Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin1@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

